INSERT INTO "texts-bc" (date, date_time, sender, message, type, sentiment) VALUES (
  '1/21/25',
  '2025-01-21 02:00:47',
  'Megan',
  'From journaling today…

Brandon told me he wasn’t coming home. 

I begged him not to give up on us and I promised that things would be different. 

That made me start thinking about why I felt like that was true. 

I think it’s because I see my role in the problem. 

Yes it’s true that I wish Brandon didn’t bring up Chris randomly in conversation but it’s up to me to handle my emotions and how I respond.

Instead of coming from a place of criticism and blame I could approach it with empathy and love. Understanding that he isn’t bringing it up to cause a fight or to hurt me. 
It simply comes from a place of uncertainty.

Instead of letting my desire to be right take over, if I stayed in my heart and remembered how much I adore, love, and respect this man I could reassure him that I belong to him.

That would fix everything. Not even fights just about this but all of them.

I don’t care about being right. I care about us being happy together.

Instead of closing off or getting aggressive when I felt hurt I need to be vulnerable and communicate.

I also realize that we process things differently and the reason he says we always fight is because he internalizes things differently than I do and it also takes a while to decompress so what seems like nothing to me is registered as a fight to him. 

At the end of the day it doesn’t matter what I think is true because perception is reality and if he perceives it to be a fight, it is so it’s my responsibility to do everything in my power to minimize those fights instead of acting like it’s nothing. 

Dear God,
Please let Brandon know how much I love him and how sorry I am for hurting him or not showing how much I appreciate everything he does for me. 

Let him know that’s so far from the truth because I know how often he puts my needs above his own and I appreciate it so much.

That’s why I sent him that song one day... because I know expressing my gratitude has been a shortcoming in our relationship but I really do notice everything he does for me.

Please give us the strength and courage to work through this and come out the other side more on love and stronger than we’ve ever been.

As sad as this has made me, there is a big part of me that’s grateful for it because it’s given me the opportunity to self reflect and I know things could truly be different this time. 

My biggest fear is that I’ve pushed him too far away. 

At the same time I also believe that love conquers all and if it’s your plan for us to be together than I’m going to do everything I can to communicate my heart to him.

At Date with Destiny I wrote my mission statement was to “Love Fearlessly”. I was thinking about Brandon when I decided on that. 

In the past it’s been so easy for me to disassociate as a defense mechanism but I’d rather risk being hurt and love fully than to settle for anything less.

Dear God please give me the strength and insight to know what I’m supposed to do because right now I feel so lost.',
  'text',
  'neutral'
);
